hopobject.body: Why did you come to ? testojack 200 The country appears to have come full circle, embracing its colonial heritage once more, and preserving its distinctive Ceylon lion identity - a heraldic symbol that adorns the national flag (above) - to represent the quality of its tea. More recently, to underline the economic importance of the trade a Ceylon planters association and tea board was created and a museum inaugurated in Kandy at which historic machinery, and artifacts pertaining to the pioneering James Taylor are displayed.
